bug.short_desc: [MediaWiki] support for nested blocks in table cells.

long_desc.thetext:
Build Identifier: This bug intend to improve the support of MediaWiki Table. Reference documentation can be found here: http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Tables This bug focuses on nested block in the table cells. Following cases are proposed: * TableWithParagraphs * TableWithLongerText * TableWithCodeInCellAndOptions * TableWithExplicitFirstRowAndRowSpan They constitute a small test suite. For each case, this bug provide: * The MediaWiki code * A screenshot produced by MediaWiki[1] (see attachment) * The HTML code produced by MediaWiki[1] (with a HTML-tidy formatting) * A RegEx Pattern against which WikiText is tested [2] [1] created with: mediawiki-1.17.0 [2] it is hard to define a good pattern to test HTML code. I have a pattern that is contained in the HTML code. It should validate against the mediaWiki raw HTML output and the tidy-formatted HTML. The idea is to test the WikiText output with org.eclipse.mylyn.wikitext.mediawiki.core.MediaWikiLanguageTest#assertContainsPattern(String, Pattern) All tables have a border attribute with value 1 to be visible in the screenshot. # Case 1: TableWithParagraphs {|border="1" | A paragraph with '''Bold text''' in a cell. | A cell ''containing'' more... Than one paragraph. |}
